import sqlite3
conn = sqlite3.connect('trivia.db')
c = conn.cursor()
c.execute("DROP TABLE attempts;")
c.execute("CREATE TABLE attempts(attempt_id integer PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT not null, user_id text, question_id int, answer text, attempt_time int, is_correct int);")
c.execute("DROP TABLE winners;")
c.execute("CREATE TABLE winners(question_id integer PRIMARY KEY, user_id text, attempt_time int, is_trivia_time int);")
c.execute("INSERT INTO winners VALUES (0,'UJ.....6V', 0, 1);")
c.execute("DROP TABLE scores;")
c.execute("CREATE TABLE scores(user_id text PRIMARY KEY, score int);")
c.execute("DROP TABLE questions;")
c.execute("CREATE TABLE questions(id int, question text, answer text, answer_pic_url text, answer_desc text);")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (0,'Test?','[\"Test\"]','','');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (1,'What percent of the Planet is water?','[70,71,72]','https://cs8.pikabu.ru/post_img/2017/04/06/1/1491431218149642992.jpg','71 Percent of the Earth''s surface is covered with water. Earth is the only planet on which water can exist in liquid form on the surface (though there may be liquid ethane or methane on Titan''s surface and liquid water beneath the surface of Europa). Liquid water is, of course, essential for life as we know it. The heat capacity of the oceans is also very important in keeping the Earth''s temperature relatively stable. Liquid water is also responsible for most of the erosion and weathering of the Earth''s continents, a process unique in the solar system today (though it may have occurred on Mars in the past).');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (2,'What industry consumes the most water? (one word)','[\"Agriculture\",\"Farming\",\"Agribusiness\"]','https://cs5.pikabu.ru/post_img/big/2015/07/20/6/1437379450_1884868655.jpg','Worldwide, agriculture accounts for 70 percent of all water consumption, compared to 20 percent for industry and 10 percent for domestic use. In industrialized nations, however, industries consume more than half of the water available for human use.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (3,'What country emit the most carbon? (one word)','[\"China\"]','https://www.ucsusa.org/sites/default/files/images/2017/11/gw-graphic-pie-chart-co2-emissions-by-country-2015.png','The picture that emerges from these figures is one where - in general - developed countries and major emerging economy nations lead in total carbon dioxide emissions. Developed nations typically have high carbon dioxide emissions per capita, while some developing countries lead in the growth rate of carbon dioxide emissions.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (4,'In which state of America did the disastrous Exxon Valdez oil spill occur? (one word)','[\"Alaska\"]','https://cs7.pikabu.ru/post_img/big/2019/06/01/7/1559389057135252663.jpg','The Exxon Valdez oil spill occurred in Prince William Sound, Alaska, March 24, 1989, when Exxon Valdez, an oil tanker owned by Exxon Shipping Company, bound for Long Beach, California, struck Prince William Sound''s Bligh Reef, 1.5 mi (2.4 km) west of Tatitlek, Alaska, at 12:04 a.m. local time and spilled 10.8 million US gallons (260,000 bbl) (or 37,000 metric tonnes) of crude oil over the next few days. It is considered to be one of the worst human-caused environmental disasters. The Valdez spill is the second largest in US waters, after the 2010 Deepwater Horizon oil spill, in terms of volume released.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (5,'What 1997 global agreement to reduce greenhouse gases was signed by virtually every country in the world except for the United States? (two words)','[\"Kyoto Protocol\"]','http://ecounion.kz/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/istock_491953254.jpg','Kyoto Protocol to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change, international treaty, named for the Japanese city in which it was adopted in December 1997, that aimed to reduce the emission of gases that contribute to global warming. In force since 2005, the protocol called for reducing the emission of six greenhouse gases in 41 countries plus the European Union to 5.2 percent below 1990 levels during the \"commitment period\" 2008–12. It was widely hailed as the most significant environmental treaty ever negotiated, though some critics questioned its effectiveness.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (6,'Which global retail chain is the largest user of green power at 310 percent of its annual electricity usage? (one word)','[\"IKEA\"]','http://ecology.md/pics/2011/12/ecoset_ikea_business_01.jpg','The global retail giant is leading the way with renewable power use in its stores and selling inexpensive home solar kits to help customers reach their goals. Thirteen retail chains in the U.S. generate 100 percent of their power from renewables.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (7,'When did the World Wildlife Fund start? (4 digits)','[1961]','https://cs8.pikabu.ru/post_img/2016/09/05/6/1473068791181545015.jpg','World Wildlife Fund was conceived in April, 1961, and set up shop in September, 1961, at IUCN''s headquarters in Morges, Switzerland. H.R.H. Prince Bernhard of the Netherlands became the organization''s first president.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (8,'What year was the first Earth Day? (4 digits)','[1970]','https://www.girlguides.ca/web/images/ggc-national/programs/specialized-programming/world-hands.png','Earth Day is an annual event celebrated around the world on April 22 to demonstrate support for environmental protection. First celebrated in 1970, it now includes events coordinated globally by the Earth Day Network in more than 193 countries.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (9,'What animal is shown fourth on the APRL organization''s logo? (one word)','[\"hare\",\"rabbit\"]','https://www.socalvegfest.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Animal-protection-and-rescue-league.png','The Animal Protection and Rescue League is a grassroots nonprofit organization with a mission to protect the rights and habitats of all animals. APRL has influenced animal protection legislation, conducted numerous animal rescues, and educated hundreds of thousands of people about humane eating.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (10,'How many oceans have become since 2000? (number)','[5,\"five\"]','https://www.worldatlas.com/aatlas/newart/oceans.gif','The surface of the planet is approximately 71% water and contains (5) five oceans, including the Arctic, Atlantic, Indian, Pacific and Southern. For many years only (4) four oceans were officially recognized, and then in the spring of 2000, the International Hydrographic Organization established the Southern Ocean, and determined its limits. Those limits include all water below 60 degrees south, and some of it, like the Arctic Ocean, is frozen.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (11,'What is the water freezing point in °Re (number)','[0,\"zero\",\"nil\",\"null\",\"O\"]','https://s18407.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/ice-water.jpg','The Réaumur scale, also known as the \"octogesimal division\", is a temperature scale for which the freezing and boiling points of water are defined as 0 and 80 degrees respectively. The scale is named for René Antoine Ferchault de Réaumur, who first proposed a similar scale in 1730.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (12,'Which country recycles the most Aluminium? (one word)','[\"Brazil\"]','https://global-recycling.info/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Aluminum_Recycling-1030x686.jpg','Brazil recycles 98.2 percent of its aluminium can production, equivalent to 14.7 billion beverage cans per year, ranking first in the world, more than Japan''s 82.5 percent recovery rate. Brazil has topped the aluminium can recycling charts eight years in a row.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (13,'What does the first letter С in the IPСС abbreviation mean? (one word)','[\"Climate\"]','https://www.umweltbundesamt.de/sites/default/files/medien/357/bilder/logo_des_ipcc_0.jpg','The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) is an intergovernmental body of the United Nations, dedicated to providing the world with an objective, scientific view of climate change, its natural, political and economic impacts and risks, and possible response options.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (14,'How many times does France fit into Great Pacific Garbage Patch? (1 digit)','[3,4,\"three\",\"four\"]','https://pbs.twimg.com/media/D4iV2cOW4AAkHMP.jpg','The Great Pacific Garbage Patch is the largest accumulation of ocean plastic in the world and is located between Hawaii and California. A huge, swirling pile of trash in the Pacific Ocean is growing faster than expected and is now three times the size of France is about 1.6 million square kilometers in size -- up to 16 times bigger than previous estimates.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (15,'What is the most toxic lake in the world? (two words)','[\"Karachay\",\"Lake Karachay\"]','https://www.theactivetimes.com/sites/default/files/uploads/1/10-shutterstock_495567157.jpg','According to a report by the Worldwatch Institute on nuclear waste, Karachay is the most polluted spot on Earth. It was used by the Soviet Union as a nuclear dumping site, and now the radiation level here is so high that it''s sufficient to give a lethal dose after just an hour of exposure.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (16,'What is the tallest waterfall in California? (two words)','[\"Yosemite Falls\",\"Yosemite\"]','https://www.worldatlas.com/r/w728-h425-c728x425/upload/23/21/8b/shutterstock-760262164.jpg','This waterfall, in the Sierra Nevada of California, is a major attraction for tourists from all around the world. The water usually peaks in the later stages of spring, between May and June, after the melting of snow. Within the same area, on the valley''s south side, the Sentinel Falls also drops from a height of about 2,000 feet between March and June with May being the peak flowing season.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (17,'Which country has built nuclear weapons and then voluntarily dismantled them in the 1990s?','[\"South Africa\",\"SA\",\"Republic of South Africa\",\"RSA\"]','https://dak95nwic4sny.cloudfront.net/73/south-africa-43313807-1533658538-ImageGalleryLightboxLarge.jpg','Six nuclear weapons were assembled. Before the anticipated changeover to a majority-elected African National Congress-led government in the 1990s, the South African government dismantled all of its nuclear weapons, the first state in the world which voluntarily gave up all nuclear arms it had developed itself.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (18,'What is the name of the bacteria that eats plastic? (two words)','[\"Ideonella sakaiensis\"]','https://3c1703fe8d.site.internapcdn.net/newman/csz/news/800/2018/howplasticea.jpg','Ideonella sakaiensis is a bacterium from the genus Ideonella and family Comamonadaceae capable of breaking down and consuming the plastic poly(ethylene terephthalate) (PET) as a sole carbon and energy source. The original Ideonella sakaiensis bacterium is far from the first living species to possess plastic-eating proclivities. Waxworm caterpillars have been found to break down plastic in a matter of hours, and mealworms possess gut microbes that eat through polystyrene.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (19,'What is the name of the major volcano that erupted in 2010? (one word)','[\"Eyjafjallajokull\",\"Eyjafjallajkull\"]','https://hiticeland.com/sites/default/files/styles/thumbnail/public/photoalbum/hiticeland_iceland_node_news_place021.jpg','Eyjafjallajökull, a volcano on the Eastern Volcanic Zone in southern Iceland, began to erupt on 14 April 2010. A plume of volcanic ash was at times ejected several kilometres into the atmosphere by this eruption, potentially causing a hazard for aeroplanes.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (20,'What kind of animals are forbidden to use for entertainment purposes in India since 2013? (one word)','[\"Dolphins\",\"Cetaceans\",\"Dolphin\",\"Cetacean\"]','http://www.hotelbellerofonte.ch/img_strutt/p450.jpg','India''s Ministry of Environment and Forests has advised state governments to ban dolphinariums and other commercial entertainment that involves the capture and confinement of cetacean species such as orcas and bottlenose dolphins. In a statement, the government said research had clearly established cetaceans are highly intelligent and sensitive, and that dolphins should be seen as *non-human persons* and as such should have their own specific rights.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (21,'Who is the most eco-friendly anti-hero in the movie Batman and Robin? (two words)','[\"Poison Ivy\",\"Ivy\"]','https://i.gifer.com/embedded/download/FjtX.gif','She is a Gotham City botanist who is obsessed with plants, ecological extinction, and environmentalism. Ivy typically wears a green one-piece outfit adorned with leaves and often has plant vines extending over her limbs. She uses plant toxins and mind-controlling pheromones for her criminal activities, which are usually aimed at protecting endangered species and the natural environment.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (22,'What was the name of the dog that helped recycle more than 26,000 plastic bottles in 6 years? (one word)','[\"Tubby\",\"Tobby\"]','http://animalworld.com.ua/images/2011/February/Animals/Record/Record_2.jpg','Most Bottles Recycled by a Dog - A Labrador called Tubby, owned by Sandra Gilmore in the UK, has helped recycle an estimated 26,000 plastic bottles over the past six years by collecting them on his daily walks, crushing them, and passing them to his owner.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (23,'Which car company was caught first in cheating with air pollution tests in 2015? (one word)','[\"Volkswagen\",\"VW\"]','https://d.newsweek.com/en/full/404907/12-10-volkswagen-04.jpg','Volkswagen has been cheating in emission tests by making its cars appear far less polluting than they are. The US Environmental Protection Agency discovered that 482,000 VW diesel cars on American roads were emitting up to 40 times more toxic fumes than permitted - and VW has since admitted the cheat affects 11m cars worldwide.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (24,'Who together with John Lennon participated in \"Bed-Ins for Peace\"? (two words)','[\"Yoko Ono\",\"his wife\",\"wife\"]','http://img.timeinc.net/time/photoessays/2009/bed_in/bed_in_01.jpg','As the Vietnam War raged in 1969, John Lennon and his wife Yoko Ono held two week-long Bed-Ins for Peace, one at the Hilton Hotel in Amsterdam and one at Fairmont The Queen Elizabeth in Montreal, each of which were intended to be non-violent protests against wars, and experimental tests of new ways to promote peace. The idea is derived from a \"sit-in\", in which a group of protesters remains seated in front of or within an establishment until they are evicted, arrested, or their demands are met.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (25,'What gliding marsupial can eat eucalyptus? (not Koala) (two words)','[\"Greater glider\",\"Greater gliders\",\"squirrel glider\",\"squirrel gliders\"]','https://d3n8a8pro7vhmx.cloudfront.net/foe/pages/444/meta_images/original/Greater_Glider_Threat_Logging.jpg','The greater glider is a small gliding marsupial found in Australia. It is nocturnal and is a solitary herbivore feeding almost exclusively on Eucalyptus leaves and buds. Like its relative the lemur-like ringtail, the greater glider is found in two forms: a sooty brown form, or a grey-to-white form.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (26,'What is used for the LA reservoir to prevent evaporation? (two words)','[\"shade balls\",\"black balls\"]','https://img1.grunge.com/img/gallery/the-real-reason-this-reservoir-is-covered-in-96000000-black-balls/intro-1559060962.jpg','The shade balls used in the Los Angeles project are made of high-density polyethylene (HDPE) with carbon black additive to protect the plastic from ultraviolet radiation. Adding carbon black also prevents the formation of bromate, a suspected human carcinogen.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (27,'What mountain is located on the border of three countries: Venezuela, Brazil, Guyana? (two words)','[\"Mount Roraima\",\"Roraima\",\"Monte Roraima\",\"Tepuy Roraima\"]','https://cameralabs.org/media/camera/aprel/23aprel/23_717e901cb18052dbee355c8772c19aa2.jpg','Mount Roraima is located on the triple border point between Brazil, Guyana and Venezuela.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (28,'Which actor who starred in the film Zombieland is the co-founder of eco-friendly paper company? (two words)','[\"Woody Harrelson\"]','https://timeecocentric.files.wordpress.com/2013/06/20130328_0071-edit.jpeg','Harrelson is a co-founder and investor in Prairie Pulp and Paper,a Canadian-based company that is developing a new form of paper that is made up of 80 percent wheat-straw waste, along with 20 percent Forest Stewardship Council certified wood fiber.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (29,'What animal was on the first version of the Greenpeace logo? (one word)','[\"dove\",\"pigeon\"]','https://i.pinimg.com/originals/46/4e/28/464e28445beec706da2953a03b8c3375.jpg','Greenpeace - white dove of peace');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (30,'What place name in Turkey translates as \"cotton castle\"? (one word)','[\"Pamukkale\"]','https://cameralabs.org/media/camera/aprel/23aprel/23_504bd1750c3a8c5592a07a6d96ab772e.jpg','Pamukkale, meaning \"cotton castle\" in Turkish, is a natural site in Denizli in southwestern Turkey. The area is famous for a carbonate mineral left by the flowing water. It is located in Turkey''s Inner Aegean region, in the River Menderes valley, which has a temperate climate for most of the year.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (31,'Who works as a safety inspector at a Springfield nuclear power plant in The Simpsons? (two words)','[\"Homer Simpson\",\"Homer\"]','https://i11d.3djuegos.com/juegos/8522/the_simpsons_tapped_out/fotos/noticias/the_simpsons_tapped_out-1933707.jpg','Homer held over 188 different jobs in the first 400 episodes of The Simpsons. In most episodes, he works as the Nuclear safety Inspector at the Springfield Nuclear Power Plant.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (32,'What event started as a lights-off in Sydney, Australia in 2007? (two words)','[\"Earth Hour\"]','https://c.ndtvimg.com/2019-03/uv6tv9s_earth-hour_625x300_30_March_19.jpg','Earth Hour is a worldwide movement organized by the World Wide Fund for Nature (WWF). The event is held annually encouraging individuals, communities, and businesses to turn off non-essential electric lights, for one hour, from 8:30 to 9:30 p.m. on a specific day towards the end of March, as a symbol of commitment to the planet.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (33,'Who invented plastic roads? (two words)','[\"Rajagopalan Vasudevan\"]','https://d1u4oo4rb13yy8.cloudfront.net/article/80302-bwpbuurzud-1517029793.jpg','This is to help overcome the growing problem of plastic waste disposal in India. The technology for this was developed by the ''Plastic Man'' of India, Prof Rajagopalan Vasudevan, Professor of Chemistry at Thiagarajar College of Engineering, Madurai.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (34,'Which is the oxidant used for purification of drinking water? (one word)','[\"ozone oxidant\",\"Ozone\",\"Ozon\",\"O3\"]','http://uborka-premium.kiev.ua/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/ozon-1024x768.jpg','Ozone (03) is the most powerful oxidant used in water purifications. It can oxidize metals (manganese,sulphur,iron ) into insoluble particles and removal from water. The removal of unwanted taste and odour is also treated by ozone oxidant.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (35,'What country is home to axolotls? (one word)','[\"Mexico\"]','https://everywherewild.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Axolotl.jpg','Although the axolotl is colloquially known as a \"walking fish\", it is not a fish, but an amphibian. The species was originally found in several lakes, such as Lake Xochimilco underlying Mexico City. Axolotls are unusual among amphibians in that they reach adulthood without undergoing metamorphosis.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (36,'Which country leads the world in electric cars per capita? (one word)','[\"Norway\"]','https://www.thelocal.no/userdata/images/article/62c5c707cc345ad7249596ca39f21278aa2d4b7ccc50541489fb87c9fa655582.jpg','Norway has the highest market penetration per capita in the world, and also has the world''s largest plug-in segment market share of new car sales, 49.1 percent in 2018. As of 2018, 10 percent of all passenger cars on Norwegian roads were plug-ins.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (37,'What country has the most rain forest? (one word)','[\"Brazil\"]','https://factslegend.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Amazon_river.jpg','The Amazon Rainforest, the largest rainforest in the world, is mostly in Brazil. Brazil has 1.2 million square miles of tropical rainforest, the most of any country in the world.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (38,'What was the most devastating hurricane in 2005? (one word)','[\"Katrina\",\"Hurricane Katrina\"]','https://www.gannett-cdn.com/media/2018/09/11/USATODAY/USATODAY/636722647770268279-091118-costliest-hurricanes-Online.png','Hurricane Katrina was an extremely destructive and deadly Category 5 hurricane that made landfall on Florida and Louisiana in August 2005, causing catastrophic damage; particularly in the city of New Orleans and the surrounding areas. Subsequent flooding, caused largely as a result of fatal engineering flaws in the flood protection system known as levees around the city of New Orleans, precipitated most of the loss of lives. The storm was the third major hurricane of the record-breaking 2005 Atlantic hurricane season, as well as the fourth-most intense Atlantic hurricane on record to make landfall in the contiguous United States, behind only the 1935 Labor Day hurricane, Hurricane Camille in 1969, and Hurricane Michael in 2018.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (39,'Which metal is used in radiation shield? (one word)','[\"lead\",\"plumbum\"]','https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Lead_shielding.jpg','Lead metal is dense; it can be used against various high-energy applications of radiation, including gamma rays, x-rays, and other types of nuclear radiation. In theory, other materials can be used for shielding during radiation, but only if the thickness is sufficient to reduce the radiation to safe limits.');")
c.execute("INSERT INTO questions VALUES (40,'What continent has most fresh water? (one word)','[\"Antarctica\"]','https://www.climate.gov/sites/default/files/NOAAClimategov_Antarctica_locator_map_620.jpg','Glaciers and ice caps cover about 10 percent of the world''s landmass. These are concentrated in Greenland and Antarctica and contain 70 percent of the world''s freshwater.');")
conn.commit()
conn.close()